## Project Status & Plan Management

`plans/STATUS.md` is the front door. Read it before suggesting work.
Active plans live in `plans/active/`, completed in `plans/shipped/`.

Every plan has two layers that must agree:

1. YAML frontmatter (machine-readable) with 7 required fields: `status`, `priority`, `owner`, `type`, `depends_on`, `blocks`, `last_updated`.
2. `## Status` banner (human-readable) showing per-phase progress and the next action.

If frontmatter and banner conflict, frontmatter wins.

When you ship a phase or merge a PR that maps to a plan:

1. Mark the phase done in the plan's `## Status` banner; highlight the next phase
2. Update `plans/STATUS.md`, move rows between "In flight" / "Recently shipped" / "Up next"
3. Bump `last_updated` in frontmatter and banner on both files
4. If the plan is fully complete: `mv plans/active/X.md plans/shipped/X.md`

Idea lifecycle:

- New idea or suggestion: add a bullet to `plans/STATUS.md` backlog section
- Only create a plan file in `plans/active/` when the idea is committed and work is starting
- Never create plan files at the repo root: `plans/active/` is the only home
- Every row in STATUS.md "In flight" or "Up next" tables MUST have a corresponding plan file

Both `plans/` directories are git-excluded: use plain `mv`, not `git mv`.
Update plans as part of the work, not as a separate ask.
